item.title: Elizabeth add a quote by Dale Carnegie
item.description: "You can conquer almost any fear if you will only make up your mind to do so. For remember, fear doesn't exist anywhere except in the mind." -- Dale Carnegie

item.title: Elizabeth add a quote by Dale Carnegie
item.description: "If you are not in the process of becoming the person you want to be, you are automatically engaged in becoming the person you don't want to be. " -- Dale Carnegie

item.title: Elizabeth add a quote by Dale Carnegie
item.description: "Success is getting what you want.. Happiness is wanting what you get." -- Dale Carnegie

item.title: Elizabeth add a quote by Dale Carnegie
item.description: "Our fatigue is often caused not by work, but by worry, frustration and resentment." -- Dale Carnegie

item.title: Elizabeth add a quote by Dale Carnegie
item.description: "Don't be afraid to give your best to what seemingly are small jobs. Every time you conquer one it makes you that much stronger. If you do the little jobs well, the big ones will tend to take care of themselves." -- Dale Carnegie

item.title: Elizabeth add a quote by Dale Carnegie
item.description: "If you can't sleep, then get up and do something instead of lying there and worrying. It's the worry that gets you, not the loss of sleep." -- Dale Carnegie

item.title: Elizabeth add a quote by Dale Carnegie
item.description: "You can sing only what you are. You can paint only what you are. You must be what your experiences, your environment, and your heredity have made you. For better or for worse, you must play your own little instrument in the orchestra of life." -- Dale Carnegie

item.title: Elizabeth add a quote by Dale Carnegie
item.description: "Be more concerned with your character than with your reputation, for your character is what you are, while your reputation is merely what others think you are." -- Dale Carnegie
